ween the carceral state and democracy in the US-a relationship that thrives to this day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPrisonszUnited StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  a1890s.  aamerica.  ableeding kansas.  ademocracy.  adesign of punishment.  afederal penitentiary.  afreedom.  ahistory.  aindian territory.  alaw.  aleavenworth.  amass incarceration.  amonuments to democracy.  anation building system.  apeculiar architecture.  apolitical significance.  apost war racial history.  aprison.  arace.  aslavery.  astate inflicted violence.  aus capitol building.  aus history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCA Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065207908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520969490zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969490zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520969490/original  a978-3-11-061013-0 EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-